bClient requests against it; do not require external services. For nativeTest on 5.0.1 / JDK 25, set runtime system properties matching the 5.0.0 scaffold: -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The current 5.0.0 build.gradle applies those native runtime properties only when libraryVersion == 5.0.0, so override runs with GVM_TCK_LV=5.0.1 can miss them.\",\n    \"Local Gradle and native-image verification remain authoritative; if those properties are insufficient, the remaining issue is likely reachability metadata rather than additional setup.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_058a4abbc603f697016a3ead2ef444819791c50c487ba7227b\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3177, "output": 825, "cacheRead": 22016, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 26018, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782492454104, "responseId": "resp_058a4abbc603f697016a3ead268b6881978eaff74fa8bbe8f5"}, "toolResults": []}
